import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('country').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    chart = sns.barplot(x='country', y='counts', data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports by country?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['state'])
    state_counts = data['state'].value_counts()
    state_counts_df = pd.DataFrame({'state': state_counts.index, 'count': state_counts.values})
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="state", y="count", data=state_counts_df)
    ax.set(xlabel='State', ylabel='Number of Airports')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports by state?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='latitude', y=data.groupby('latitude').size().values, data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport locations by latitude?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['longitude'])
    sns.scatterplot(x='longitude', y=data.groupby('longitude').size().index, size=data.groupby('longitude').size().values, sizes=(20, 200), legend=False)
    plt.axvline(x=data['longitude'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['longitude'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport locations by longitude?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width = 800, height = 800, 
                background_color ='white', 
                stopwords = [], 
                min_font_size = 10).generate(' '.join(data['name']))
    plt.imshow(wordcloud)
    plt.axis("off")
    plt.tight_layout(pad = 0)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport names?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
